cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper focuses on learning a motion model from visual observations, specifically monocular camera images. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an end-to-end trainable architecture for learning the motion model, which involves training a deep neural network. 
3. cs.RO (Robotics): The learned motion model is intended for use in autonomous driving, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper involves developing a model for intelligent behavior (driving) based on learning from data. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper mentions leveraging scene segmentation side tasks to improve performance, which involves natural language processing techniques.
